reviews.text: You can find seats even during peak hours. Good food

Nice place. Relatively silent place compared with other parts of the city. With seating out areas specially welcomed by elderly people. Dogs are not allowed to be kept in the estate,   but wildlife like monkey and wild pig are frequently seen seeking their food nearby. The sound generated by insects and bullfrog can be heard near the hillside in summer nights, just like the countryside.
The boundary of the estate is now fully fenced off from the woodland. Hikers could take the service road of the water reservoir to access the trails on the north slope of the Lion Rock.
Great air quality and with a scene. Right under the Lion Rock.
Pretty run down building and you need to transfer on the 201 to get here from MTR.
